400g water
fresh madre
520g flour (120 whole grain, 400 bl80)
10g salt after fermentolyzis
1g ascorbic acid
some small 10-20 batches during bassagne
first bassagne with water and salt, then add oil, then water, then oil, then water until its soft but tough
window test for glucozis
preheat oven with 250ml water and iron to 265 'C
wash jiggly bread with water
cut an ear and tattoe a grain
10 min on 265 'C
42 min on 195 'C
rest it on gitter wire
